Read SKILL-landing-brief.md in the current folder.
Read ./web-artifacts-builder/SKILL.md

Then do the following steps in order:

STEP 1 — Initialize the React project:
Run: bash ./web-artifacts-builder/scripts/init-artifact.sh transnatur-landing

STEP 2 — Install react-router-dom:
cd transnatur-landing && npm install react-router-dom

STEP 3 — Configure Tailwind with custom colors and fonts.
In tailwind.config.ts add:
- colors: navy #0B1F3A, red #C62828, gray #4A444A, light #F5F5F5
- fontFamily: heading = Poppins, label = Bebas Neue

STEP 4 — Add Google Fonts to index.html:
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@800&family=Bebas+Neue&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

STEP 5 — Create these files in src/pages/:
- Home.tsx — full landing page with all sections from the brief
- Form.tsx — lead form page with all fields from the brief
- ThankYou.tsx — thank you page

STEP 6 — Set up routing in App.tsx using react-router-dom.
Routes: / → Home, /form → Form, /thankyou → ThankYou

STEP 7 — Copy images to the project:
Copy ../assets/ folder into transnatur-landing/src/assets/

STEP 8 — Bundle everything into one HTML file:
Run: bash ../web-artifacts-builder/scripts/bundle-artifact.sh

STEP 9 — Show me the bundle.html file.